IO_SystemDataRQ/RS - Old


Target audience

MICE, RMS

Version

1.0.

Authentication

Bearer Token

Message type

Pull, Asynchronous, Inbound

Message description


Result message to hold all categories of requested system data. Note: if you do not provide at least one of the elements Accounting, Profiles, Loyalty, Rooms, Reservations, Events, Rates or Tasks in your request, the RS message will hold all data.

Used to match result messages (*RS) to request messages (*RQ) in asynchronous communication patterns. Therefore mandatory.

IO_SystemDataRS - Attributes

Push message to hold all categories of requested system data

  • Accounting information 
  • Profiles information
  • Loyalty information
  • Rooms information
  • Reservations information
  • Events information
  • Rates information
  • Tasks information

IO_SystemDataRS | Warnings | Warning

1..n

Single warning element


@Code

0..1

If present, this refers to a table of coded values exchanged between applications to identify errors or warnings. Refer to OpenTravel Alliance Code List Error Codes (ERR).


@Type

0..1

The Error element MUST contain the Type attribute that uses a recommended set of values to indicate the error type. The validating XSD can expect to accept values that it has NOT been explicitly coded for and process them by using Type ="Unknown". Refer to OpenTravel Code List Error Warning Type (EWT).


@ShortText

0..1

An abbreviated version of the error in textual format.
